### Instruction:
Who was the president of the United States in 1996?

### Response:

The President of the United States in 1996 was Bill Clinton. He served as the 42nd President of the United States from 1993 to 2001, and his second term ended on January 20th, 2001. In 1996, he ran for re-election against Republican candidate Bob Dole and won a second term in office.
